column5: Went to Barrie on Monday and ended up getting a bunch of keepers and one pushing 10-10.5".  I was the one with the german sheppard who decided to go for a swim off the dock.  Kinda tired with the non stop dink fest.  ANy other suggestions for fast and furious keepers??? Thanx in advance.
o so that was ur dog lol
I hear in the spring you can get some real nice ones at the narrows betweem simcoe and Cooch, not sure what the action would be like there now though.
U could give the hamilton inner bay atry... sometimes they are hard to find but there are usually some really nice ones to be had without the dinks.
